From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Amaan Qureshi <git@amaanq.com>
Date: Sat, 26 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] r8125: disable vendor /proc debug files

cachyos/0018 imports the Realtek out-of-tree r8125 driver, which
unconditionally creates world-readable (S_IRUGO) entries under
/proc/net/r8125/<iface>/debug and .../test that dump device registers,
descriptor rings, and EEPROM contents. The procfs define is gated on
LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= 2.4.37, which is always true on modern kernels,
so every build ships those debug files.

There is no upside to keeping them on a hardened kernel: they are
vendor-internal debug aids, not part of any userspace ABI, and exposing
them widens the attack surface for any process able to read /proc/net.
Disable the feature outright; all call sites in the driver are already
#ifdef ENABLE_R8125_PROCFS so this leaves the proc-creation paths as
dead code.

---
 drivers/net/ethernet/realtek/r8125.h | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/realtek/r8125.h b/drivers/net/ethernet/realtek/r8125.h
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/realtek/r8125.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/realtek/r8125.h
@@ -468,6 +468,7 @@
 #if LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(2,4,37)
 #define ENABLE_R8125_PROCFS
 #endif
+#undef ENABLE_R8125_PROCFS

 #if LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(3,11,0)
 #define ENABLE_R8125_SYSFS
--
2.52.0
